						<summary>

						<p>This is a damaged inscription. It seems to record a gift of gold left with the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Tirutturutti for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple with an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee every day, by <hi rend="bold">Parāntakaṉ Aṟiñjigai</hi> (evidently <hi rend="bold">prince Ariñjaya</hi>). This is assignable to <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
